<br>
As most of you know I was away for a long time due to some difficult RL things. When I returned I felt like the spark had gone out of Norrath, As it did so many years ago on a small island north of France, when the old ways gave in to the new. It has become painfully obvious to me that norrath, aye not even Qeynos, needs me anymore. And if there is one thing a paladin needs, besides Karanas rain on his face, it's to be needed.<br>
<br>
I have heard much of a realm that may be in need of a paladin of the old ways, and have decided to travel there and see if this is in fact true. And perhaps even rebuild a Steel Menage there.<br>
If the Norrathian Menage is to survive, it will require leadership, I have instructed my squire Johe to stay behind and hand over this leadership to whoever feels they may be such a leader, and then he is to follopw me into the mysts.<br>
<br>
Know this, I have never appreciated, and respected, nay, loved, a ragtag group of adventurers as I have each and every one of you, the trully impossible concept that is the Steel Menage was made a reality because of you all.<br>
But now a thunderhead has formed on the horizon, and I somehow know that I must follow it to my new calling.<br>
<br>
The mighty Karana bless and keep you all.<br>
In the near future, before I leave the confines of Norrath once and for all, I will call out to you all one last time, and I pray you will come and accept the few belongings I have so they can be used against evil in my absense. For I must undertake this quest with nothing but my wits. <p>Rafferty Thunderheart
Paladin of the mighty Karana
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugrymwyll.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grymwyll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#E6E8fA>(1/7/02 2:07:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fsteelmenagetheboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=60.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The End of an Era</span><hr size=1> Rafferty,<br>
<br>
