<br>
Ah am Grymwyll, an' in case ye may, er may nay woot (know) Ah am the 'umble paladin who took in Ezmeres when 'e transcended realms an' found 'is way into Albion. <br>
<br>
(but the same person who played Ez, Grymstout, Aertemis and etc...)<br>
<br>
Let mae juste sayeth that ye are entirely ryghte that all goode things must endeth.  Ah know from lore an' per'aps 'istory that even the epic myghte o' Arthur's Rounde Table cayme te end, an' all that is left in Camelot is a shadow o' its former glory.<br>
<br>
Greede, selfishness, an' thus the corruptibility o' the 'uman ( er elven, er any sentient creature) soul spawns an' lives either in ful force or in the shadows o' e'ery civilization or society that exists.  Therefore it is up te us te constantly fyghte this corruptibility by strivin' inwardly te become as ful o' virtue as conceivably possible.<br>
<br>
